dataIdInfo.idAbs: This feature class contains the road networks, including links or roads that connect from one road type to another road type of the same or lower designation, of all countries in Africa, extracted from the OpenStreetMap geodatabase (OSM GeoDB, as of April, 2020), and downloaded via https://download.geofabrik.de/. The dataset includes roads designated as the following feature classes in the OSM GeoDB: motorway (/highway), motorway link, trunk (important roads), trunk link, primary (typically national level roads), primary link, secondary (typically regional level roads), and secondary link. Roads designated as "motorway" and "trunk" are divided and mapped individually as one-way roads. Features with a designation of "link" are sections of road that connect from one road to another road of equal or lesser category (equivalent to a highway entrance or exit ramp in the United States). Complete documentation for the attributes associated with these data can be found at https://download.geofabrik.de/osm-data-in-gis-formats-free.pdf. The data have been modified from their original format to fit the structure and schema of this geodatabase (e.g. attribute field names and some attributes have been renamed or reformatted, some original attribute fields have been omitted in this compilation, new fields have been created to include source and other relevant information, and roads for all countries in Africa have been grouped together by type within this geodatabase); descriptive field aliases were created from the original field names in the source data.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Road (motorway, trunk, primary, and secondary roads, including their links) transportation network of Africa stored as polylines in the feature class "AFR_Infra_Transport_Road" for use in a geographic information system (GIS). This feature class includes road networks that are designated as motorway, motorway link, trunk, trunk link, "primary," "primary link," "secondary," and "secondary link" feature classes in the OpenStreetMap road database.
